The paper deals with the computational complexity of a problem related to self-assembly of tiles, which involves combinatorial and geometric aspects. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Symbolic Computation (cs.SC) categories. Additionally, since the paper focuses on the NP-hardness of the problem, it may also belong to the Complexity Theory (cs.CC) category.
